Brazil February Job Creation May Have Been Record, Folha Reports

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-03-10T16:15:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/brazil-february-job-creation-may-have-been-record-folha-reports.html
  Brazil  may have created a record
number of jobs in February, Folha de S.Paulo newspaper said,
citing an interview with Labor Minister Carlos Lupi.  The South American country last month may have registered
nearly 210,000 so-called formal work positions with the
government, Folha quoted Lupi as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
 idantas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Faries at 
 wfaries@bloomberg.net  